Subject: PCB - SPO Teams Channels AIC No Activity
Description:
Customer: Post Consumer Brands/Post Holdings

Hello Support,

After upgrading to NEA 11.6.0.112 and then clearing tier1/2 DBs for SharePoint then running fresh SPAA and SPAC jobs we are not seeing activity within Teams Channels for users. Within the DB it appears the resourceid on that activity is NULL. Which makes sense as to why it does not show within AIC.

Name                                          Version    InstallDate
----                                          -------    -----------
Netwrix Access Information Center             11.6.0.25  20241004   
Netwrix Activity Monitor                      7.0.3175   20241004   
Netwrix Activity Monitor Agent 64-bit         7.0.3175   20241004   
Netwrix Enterprise Auditor V11.6              11.6.0.112 20241004   
Netwrix Sensitive Data Discovery Add-On V11.6 11.6.0.13  20241004

Thank you,
Justin
DevOps_Steps_to_Reproduce__c:
Upgrade NEA to 11.6.0.112
Remove all tables and SQLlite dbs related to sharepoint
Scan and import SP permissions and activity
Note resourceid of activity records is null
What_We_Know__c:
Issues like this often occur when a customer has conducted an SPAC scan that gathered activity involving SP resources that havenâ€™t yet been scanned with SPAA or SPSEEK. If they are reviewing this activity in the AIC immediately after importing the SPAC scan data, it could explain why the ResourceIds are null. Running an SPAA or SPSEEK scan with those resources included and then importing the results should resolve the issue.

Let me know if you continue to se the NULLs after running SPAA/SPSEEK.

"I opened this case after multiple SPAA/SPEEK runs, this is still a problem."
Next_Steps__c:
Verify the following with customer:
* Are the following event IDs present in SA_SPAC_ActivityEventsView: 3992693, 8400059, 12642013
* Is the SPAA/SPSEEK scan scoped to include the paths of SPAC?
Solution_Comment__c: Partner has done several updates and data drops and is no longer seeing the issue. We're not sure what resolved it, but ok to close. Will reopen if the issue returns.
